1.title: When Tailored Chic Meets Normcore: Bryanboy and NYU Singer Make Sweet Music

episode of.title: Bryan Boy Goes to College (TV Mini-Series 2014– )

1.plot: Fashion blogger Bryanboy meets up with Madison, an NYU student who is studying recorded music, to talk fashion and dorm room style. Explaining her preference for wearing all black, Madison breaks from her norm and rocks a pink skirt by Kelly Wearstler. She and Bryanboy cap off the episode by singing a catchy duet!

4.title: How to Translate Trends for College Life with the NYU Fashion Magazine's Creative Director

episode of.title: Bryan Boy Goes to College (TV Mini-Series 2014– )

4.plot: When it comes to making runway looks work for class, there may be no one better at it than NYU student Olivia Perez. As the creative director of Embodied, Olivia enjoys taking high fashion and re-working it for a student in the city. Watch as she gives Bryanboy a peek at her (highly organized) designer-filled closet.

5.title: Style Secrets from a Global Design Student Who Makes Her Own Pants

episode of.title: Bryan Boy Goes to College (TV Mini-Series 2014– )

5.plot: Lea is a sophomore at Parsons The New School for Design who has lived in Taiwan, Paris, Las Vegas, and New York. She brings her travel experience to her fashion work, and enjoys wearing custom-designed pieces. See how Bryanboy's global fashion knowledge stacks up against Lea's!

6.title: The Need to Know Styling Tricks of a Parsons Design Student

episode of.title: Bryan Boy Goes to College (TV Mini-Series 2014– )

6.plot: According to Osve, a product design student at Parsons The New School for Design, there's nothing typical about the way students at her college dress. With their inherent creativity comes a close attention to detail and a pride in showcasing unique personal style. Find out some of the fashion ruses Osve employs to create her put-together ensembles.

8.plot: Fashion is a passion for Solomon, a freshman at Marymount Manhattan College, and in order to afford his fixation on style he aims to become a lawyer after college. Bryanboy meets up with the political science major at Strand Book Store to talk style, budgeting, and how to dominate the runway.
